{
  "stem": "26142.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this-- this was a unique-- unique school, because in the entire Carpathian region, in small places like Torun, there were no Hebrew schools.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The only place that had a Hebrew school was cities like Munkacs and Chust or Sevlus.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The-- and also, they-- the schools that they had became were organized later.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The school-- and the Hebrew school in Torum for some reason was already, in 1920, in existence.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was, in general, like I said the-- the public schools was Ruthenian and Czech.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And most-- most of the population in the small villages-- because villages like Torun were dotted all the way to the this city of Chust, which was west of Torun about 87 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Some had more or less between 2,000 and 3,000 populations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The Jewish population varied.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the next village, which was only four kilometers from Torun, was called Brzesc.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they only had about 100 Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But the interesting thing about it was that in Brzesc, there was no Zionist movement.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And in Torun, there was a Zionist organization, the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they were the ones that-- with the help-- I think they did get help from the American Joint Distribution Committee to organize the Hebrew school in Torun.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In general, the children went to public school a half a day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And after they went out from public school, they went to cheder That that was the-- the-- the education that they got.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And that was the main-- the main emphasis that people had for education.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It was not the secular education, but the Jewish education-- the Hebrew-- and of course, that higher education was already the Yeshivas, which some of them were very, very famous.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The most famous one was like the one in [?",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
